An Ivorian woman was Saturday morning arrested at the Moi International Airport, Mombasa while carrying heroin valued at more than Sh10 million.Danho Bertille, 28 was headed for Abdijan through JKIA when her luggage was found with the drugs. It&#39;s not clear where she got the drugs but it&#39;s an indication the source is in Mombasa. Danho BertillePolice are interrogating the woman to know the source and those involved. Cases of drug trafficking have been on the rise in the area with few arrests.